WEBVTT

00:31.866 --> 00:34.802
<i>Once</i>
<i>it was a family of pioneers.</i>

00:39.874 --> 00:41.609
<i>They were looking</i>
<i>for a better life.</i>

00:56.858 --> 00:58.425
<i>The family came from a big city,</i>

00:59.594 --> 01:01.829
<i>but then they ran out of money</i>
<i>and they had to leave.</i>

01:09.003 --> 01:12.172
<i>There was a big sister</i>
<i>and a little sister.</i>

01:13.641 --> 01:15.677
<i>There was a mom and a dad.</i>

01:17.244 --> 01:19.179
<i>They weren't perfect.</i>

01:19.313 --> 01:20.548
<i>But they were a family.</i>

01:30.123 --> 01:31.258
<i>...and</i>
<i>are throwing in the towel.</i>

01:31.391 --> 01:33.160
<i>The indicators are right there.</i>

01:33.293 --> 01:36.396
<i>We have the highest</i>
<i>unemployment in-</i>

01:36.531 --> 01:38.332
<i>and growing segment</i>
<i>of the population</i>

01:38.465 --> 01:41.201
<i>who are taking out more</i>
<i>than they are putting in</i>

01:41.335 --> 01:44.539
<i>at a national debt</i>
<i>that outweighs our GDP.</i>

01:44.672 --> 01:48.009
<i>Folks, we are living</i>
<i>in a house of cards.</i>

01:48.141 --> 01:50.511
<i>And when the walls</i>
<i>come tumbling down...</i>

01:54.849 --> 01:59.286
Riley, we can't leave
without you.

02:00.922 --> 02:02.322
You'd never survive on your own.

02:04.058 --> 02:05.158
I would.

02:05.292 --> 02:06.426
Oh, yeah?

02:06.561 --> 02:08.029
What would you eat?

02:08.161 --> 02:09.363
Cereal.

02:09.496 --> 02:10.832
There's three boxes
in the kitchen.

02:12.567 --> 02:14.869
All right, Cap'n Crunch.
Let's roll.

02:17.071 --> 02:18.305
This is home.

02:22.275 --> 02:25.847
No, home
is where we're together.

02:29.117 --> 02:30.350
Promise?

02:57.512 --> 03:00.280
Vroom, vroom,
vroom, vroom, vroom.

03:05.019 --> 03:08.255
Vroom, vroom, vroom,
vroom, vroom.

03:10.024 --> 03:11.526
How you girls
doing back there?

03:13.161 --> 03:14.428
After we move,

03:14.562 --> 03:15.930
are you going to have a job
like before?

03:17.397 --> 03:18.933
Not right away.
You know, unless I want one.

03:20.134 --> 03:21.334
You know why?

03:21.468 --> 03:24.105
Because we're going on
an adventure.

03:24.237 --> 03:26.007
You know adventurers, right?

03:26.140 --> 03:27.374
Like a Tarzan.

03:27.508 --> 03:28.843
Yeah, sure.

03:28.976 --> 03:30.410
Yeah, like a Tarzan.

03:30.545 --> 03:31.846
I like the monkeys.

03:35.883 --> 03:37.618
Mommy...

04:16.256 --> 04:18.993
<i>People out there</i>
<i>are pissed off.</i>

04:19.127 --> 04:21.294
<i>They've lost homes, businesses,</i>

04:21.428 --> 04:23.430
<i>and they're not taking it</i>
<i>anymore.</i>

04:23.564 --> 04:24.899
<i>The phone lines are blowing up.</i>

04:25.032 --> 04:27.101
<i>Let's go to Dennis in Milwaukee.</i>
<i>What's up, man?</i>

04:27.235 --> 04:29.302
<i>Jerry, look,</i>
<i>we're going to talk about</i>

04:29.436 --> 04:30.772
<i>what the last caller was saying.</i>

04:30.905 --> 04:32.305
<i>I gotta...</i>

04:47.822 --> 04:49.223
When can I play?

04:49.356 --> 04:51.025
Never.

04:51.159 --> 04:52.527
Why?

04:52.660 --> 04:54.762
Your brain
is still little and stupid.

04:54.896 --> 04:57.297
Someday it'll grow up
and it'll work better.

04:57.430 --> 04:58.633
Riley, share with your sister.

04:58.766 --> 05:00.268
She doesn't even know
how to play.

05:00.400 --> 05:01.803
She just wants to press buttons.

05:03.470 --> 05:04.739
-Uh, excuse me.
-Yeah.

05:06.207 --> 05:09.309
Yeah. My husband and I, we split
the combo number one,

05:09.442 --> 05:10.878
but we didn't get
the hash browns

05:11.012 --> 05:12.880
since he had chose
the hash browns.

05:13.014 --> 05:14.982
Yeah, that's just
how they do it.

05:15.116 --> 05:16.584
All combos are $7.99.

05:16.717 --> 05:18.052
Doesn't really matter
if you get everything or not.

05:18.186 --> 05:19.921
I just don't want
to pay for the hash browns.

05:20.054 --> 05:21.222
Will you take it off?

05:21.354 --> 05:22.355
-Like I said, the-
-You know what?

05:22.489 --> 05:24.025
I'd love to have
the hash browns.

05:24.158 --> 05:25.226
Thank you.

05:25.358 --> 05:26.561
Be right out.

05:35.870 --> 05:37.872
Mom.

05:38.005 --> 05:39.040
Mary!

05:40.141 --> 05:41.341
Mommy, look.

05:43.778 --> 05:45.246
It's name is Cookie.

05:45.378 --> 05:46.781
Baby, you...
you can't do that, okay?

05:46.914 --> 05:48.683
I love riding her.
She's very pretty.

05:48.816 --> 05:50.383
-And I love braiding her hair.
-Okay?

05:53.287 --> 05:57.158
She comes from Unicorn Land
and she's a very rare unicorn.

05:57.291 --> 05:58.458
She's very pretty.

06:23.818 --> 06:25.920
♪ I woke up this morning ♪

06:26.053 --> 06:28.388
♪ And found a note on my head ♪

06:28.522 --> 06:29.957
♪ Said I'm leaving you, baby ♪

06:30.091 --> 06:32.459
♪ And I'm leaving you
a whole can of beans ♪

06:32.593 --> 06:34.562
♪ And then I drove
my pickup truck ♪

06:34.695 --> 06:36.530
♪ Down to the corner store ♪

06:36.664 --> 06:38.833
♪ And got myself some beers ♪

06:38.966 --> 06:41.636
♪ But I had to lay
my woman down ♪

06:41.769 --> 06:44.805
♪ Because she's bugging me
all around town ♪

06:44.939 --> 06:47.008
♪ That is what she does ♪

06:47.141 --> 06:50.611
♪ And I left you
an old can of beans ♪

06:50.745 --> 06:52.179
♪ Yes ♪

07:27.381 --> 07:28.816
Guys, we're here.

07:52.606 --> 07:53.975
What is this place?

07:55.242 --> 07:56.476
Home.

08:40.621 --> 08:42.556
Pipe wrench.
I'll get you.

08:47.361 --> 08:48.629
What do you think?

08:48.763 --> 08:50.197
Call it a day?

08:50.331 --> 08:51.899
I'm not tired.

08:52.033 --> 08:54.402
It's because you're not the one
on top of the house.

08:54.535 --> 08:55.803
First lesson
of upper management.

08:57.004 --> 08:59.707
Respect union breaks
or the workers will strike.

09:03.177 --> 09:04.211
Thanks, hon.

09:06.714 --> 09:07.915
Hey, little monster.

09:08.049 --> 09:09.216
Get over here
and finish your food.

09:16.357 --> 09:17.625
What, you don't like it?

09:17.758 --> 09:18.859
Tomatoes are gross.

09:18.993 --> 09:21.062
What? No. They're so good.

09:27.435 --> 09:28.803
When do we go back to school?

09:34.942 --> 09:36.644
What if you don't have to?

09:38.145 --> 09:39.814
What if you could
just stay up here?

09:39.947 --> 09:41.582
Kids have to go to school.

09:44.118 --> 09:45.286
Okay.

09:46.555 --> 09:47.755
Then this is a school.

09:48.656 --> 09:49.757
What is?

09:49.890 --> 09:51.459
This cabin.

09:51.592 --> 09:55.463
It can be a school. It can be
whatever you want it to be.

09:55.596 --> 09:57.932
-Really?
-Mary likes it.

10:03.337 --> 10:06.140
If you could learn about
anything, what would it be?

10:08.409 --> 10:10.311
I like history.

10:11.779 --> 10:13.080
Then we'll learn history.

10:16.717 --> 10:18.319
Your mom and I, we had two jobs

10:18.452 --> 10:21.122
so we could buy groceries
that somebody else grew.

10:21.255 --> 10:23.057
Send you to school
where somebody else taught.

10:24.058 --> 10:25.226
And it was backwards.

10:26.994 --> 10:29.997
We make the rules now.
All four of us.

10:31.799 --> 10:33.334
<i>This place, it's just us.</i>

10:35.202 --> 10:36.170
<i>It's ours.</i>

11:08.068 --> 11:11.939
Oh. Mm.
Pew. Pew, pew. Pew. Pew.

11:17.111 --> 11:19.947
Now what?
Nothing. You exploded.

11:22.016 --> 11:23.817
When do you explode?

11:23.951 --> 11:26.020
I don't. I'm the American.

11:26.153 --> 11:27.321
You're the Taliban.

11:29.957 --> 11:31.158
Oh, okay.
One, two, three.

11:40.801 --> 11:43.370
<i>When the early pioneers</i>
<i>went west, life was hard.</i>

11:44.606 --> 11:47.074
<i>Many spent all their money</i>
<i>on the trip</i>

11:47.208 --> 11:49.611
<i>and had nothing left</i>
<i>when they got there.</i>

11:49.743 --> 11:51.178
<i>They were everyday Americans</i>

11:51.312 --> 11:54.381
<i>who risked everything</i>
<i>for an uncertain reward.</i>

11:55.816 --> 11:57.284
The frontire was a-

11:57.418 --> 11:58.986
Frontier.

11:59.119 --> 12:01.255
The I-E-R is like ear.

12:03.090 --> 12:04.992
The frontier was...

12:17.505 --> 12:19.873
Well, what do you guys
want on the flag?

12:20.007 --> 12:21.342
Can there be stars?

12:21.475 --> 12:22.409
How many?

12:22.544 --> 12:24.144
Four?

12:24.278 --> 12:26.146
Why four?

12:26.280 --> 12:27.748
Four of us.

12:29.450 --> 12:30.484
I like pirates.

12:30.619 --> 12:32.453
Like a skull and crossbones?

12:32.587 --> 12:34.455
No, no, no!

12:34.589 --> 12:36.457
Your sister is afraid
of skeletons.

12:36.591 --> 12:38.225
You said
it could be anything.

12:38.359 --> 12:40.394
Anything that doesn't
involve skeletons or the undead.

12:42.863 --> 12:44.131
Sharks.

12:51.839 --> 12:52.973
Sharks we can do.

13:04.753 --> 13:07.054
<i>You look like a man</i>
<i>with a question.</i>

13:07.187 --> 13:09.223
<i>What does that look like?</i>

13:09.356 --> 13:14.228
Hmm. Pensive, squinty eyes,
maybe a little constipated.

13:14.361 --> 13:15.429
Really?

13:19.366 --> 13:20.901
Are you okay?

13:21.035 --> 13:22.336
Better than okay.

13:26.040 --> 13:28.042
Do you think this place
is good for you?

13:28.175 --> 13:29.577
Is it, is it helping?

13:33.113 --> 13:34.348
Hmm.
I love you.

13:34.481 --> 13:35.482
And I love you, too.

14:01.241 --> 14:02.610
Spotted a base command.

14:02.744 --> 14:04.078
We have eyes on target.

14:04.211 --> 14:06.146
Be advised. He has a weapon.

14:06.280 --> 14:08.683
May need air support. Over.

14:35.610 --> 14:36.644
Good afternoon.

14:37.812 --> 14:38.946
You got a minute?

14:39.079 --> 14:40.414
I'm with Building and Safety.

14:42.751 --> 14:45.919
I was up here for an inspection
three or four years back.

14:47.488 --> 14:49.089
The place was already
in foreclosure then

14:49.223 --> 14:51.091
but it looked like hell.

14:51.225 --> 14:52.761
Yeah, I found some
spare lumber around the place,

14:52.893 --> 14:54.294
you know, fixed what I could.

14:56.029 --> 14:57.264
Power come off the grid?

14:57.398 --> 14:58.966
Yep.
Hoping to go solar, though.

14:59.834 --> 15:01.034
Phone?

15:01.168 --> 15:03.103
Uh, old landline hookup.

15:03.237 --> 15:05.005
And where's your septic?

15:07.174 --> 15:08.475
Uh... over there, I think.

15:14.582 --> 15:16.518
Yeah.

15:16.651 --> 15:18.051
You smell that?

15:18.185 --> 15:20.053
You got a leak.

15:20.187 --> 15:21.188
You're gonna need
to dig out the tank,

15:21.321 --> 15:23.390
patch it, maybe replace.

15:26.728 --> 15:28.028
Come on.

15:28.162 --> 15:30.464
You've got farms in the valley.

15:30.598 --> 15:32.266
County considers
cross-contamination

15:32.399 --> 15:34.001
to be an E. coli risk.

15:35.169 --> 15:37.037
Previous owner probably
got grandfathered in.

15:38.038 --> 15:39.940
I... I got to dig it out myself?

15:40.073 --> 15:41.475
You got a winch?

15:41.609 --> 15:43.611
-No.
-You're going to need a winch.

15:46.815 --> 15:48.081
It's bullshit.

15:48.215 --> 15:50.284
No, that is your shit

15:50.417 --> 15:52.219
running into the county's
water table.

15:59.159 --> 16:00.360
Fuck's sake!

16:12.139 --> 16:13.508
What do you think
they look like?

16:13.641 --> 16:15.108
Do you think
that they're yellow?

16:15.242 --> 16:16.711
You think they're orange?

16:16.845 --> 16:19.714
How do you not know
what a monkey looks like?

16:45.807 --> 16:47.040
Mary!

16:54.849 --> 16:58.252
Mary! Mary!

17:00.522 --> 17:02.256
Mary!

17:02.389 --> 17:05.527
She said there weren't,
but I think I found one.

17:05.660 --> 17:07.562
Have you seen any in the trees?

17:08.763 --> 17:11.031
I think they only come out
at night.

17:11.164 --> 17:12.734
And that's why
nobody's seen them.

17:16.871 --> 17:18.138
Is she with you?

17:22.142 --> 17:23.377
I'm Eric.

17:25.947 --> 17:27.615
Riley.

17:27.749 --> 17:29.684
Well, Riley,

17:29.817 --> 17:32.520
you gonna give her
the bad news about the monkeys?

17:32.654 --> 17:34.154
Or am I gonna have
to be the one?

17:39.761 --> 17:41.361
So it's a night
before Thanksgiving.

17:41.495 --> 17:42.830
We got some family
coming into town.

17:42.964 --> 17:45.800
So Susie cooks up everything
the day before,

17:45.934 --> 17:49.971
the bird, mashed potatoes,
cornbread, that works.

17:50.103 --> 17:52.439
That night I wake up,

17:52.574 --> 17:55.510
I hear this crashing
coming from downstairs.

17:55.643 --> 17:57.645
It's like a marching band's
moving in.

17:57.779 --> 17:59.547
Now I just figured
it was Susie, right?

17:59.681 --> 18:03.383
Figured she was putting the last
minute touches on the meal.

18:04.886 --> 18:06.654
Then I hear this deep,

18:06.788 --> 18:11.224
deep grumbling inches
from the back of my neck.

18:12.961 --> 18:14.161
Oh. Was it a monster?

18:14.294 --> 18:16.731
It was worse.

18:16.864 --> 18:18.866
It was Susie snoring.

18:20.133 --> 18:21.101
I do not.

18:29.376 --> 18:32.080
So then I go downstairs, right?

18:32.212 --> 18:34.682
The fridge is wide open,
and I kid you not,

18:34.816 --> 18:37.217
there is this guy
gorging his face,

18:37.351 --> 18:39.020
going to town on Susie's food.

18:39.186 --> 18:42.422
And I'm like, "Hey, buddy,
that's our Thanksgiving dinner."

18:42.557 --> 18:44.324
Well, what did he say?

18:44.458 --> 18:46.694
"The neighbor's food
was better."

18:47.962 --> 18:49.864
He's like, "The neighbor's
food was better."

18:49.998 --> 18:51.733
"Get the hell out of my house."

18:53.935 --> 18:56.671
Yeah. That's when we decided
that Tampa wasn't for us.

18:56.804 --> 18:57.872
Too many lunatics.

18:58.006 --> 18:59.741
Those people
should be permanently locked up,

18:59.874 --> 19:01.174
as far as I'm concerned.

19:02.744 --> 19:04.579
- Bourbon?
- Oh, yes.

19:05.880 --> 19:07.081
Hey, old man.

19:07.214 --> 19:09.851
Pour me up a tall one
on the rocks.

19:11.586 --> 19:12.954
Have you all seen
the bear that's been

19:13.087 --> 19:14.421
roaming around here?

19:16.057 --> 19:18.059
You walk all the way
down to the creek.

19:18.191 --> 19:19.226
There's a little waterfall,
but you-

19:19.359 --> 19:20.695
Guns are bad.

19:24.832 --> 19:29.570
Well, uh, guns can be bad,
but if it's used correctly,

19:29.704 --> 19:32.272
it's just a tool,
like a screwdriver.

19:32.406 --> 19:33.908
Or like a pipe wrench.

19:35.877 --> 19:36.911
That too.

19:46.921 --> 19:48.890
I'm sorry if I made anyone
feel uncomfortable.

19:49.023 --> 19:51.826
I'm used to carrying it
everywhere.

19:51.959 --> 19:53.226
I'm sorry.

19:53.360 --> 19:54.696
Nah. We're a bunch
of city folk talking.

19:57.699 --> 19:59.299
<i>We made a mistake, babe.</i>
<i>We're going home.</i>

19:59.433 --> 20:01.536
<i>The girls</i>
<i>are having fun out here.</i>

20:01.669 --> 20:04.371
<i>I like it, and I think</i>
<i>it's great to be up here.</i>

20:04.505 --> 20:05.773
Is Mom okay?

20:05.907 --> 20:07.441
<i>And we do not</i>
<i>have to deal</i>

20:07.575 --> 20:09.177
<i>with the real world right now,</i>
<i>okay?</i>

20:09.309 --> 20:10.745
<i>That is the best for you.</i>
<i>We moved up here for you.</i>

20:10.878 --> 20:12.680
- <i>You understand that?</i>
-She'll be fine.

20:12.814 --> 20:14.481
<i>We're nothing</i>
<i>like these peoples!</i>

20:15.683 --> 20:16.651
<i>We're going back...</i>

20:16.784 --> 20:18.351
She'll be better in the morning.

20:18.485 --> 20:19.921
<i>We're going</i>
<i>to figure it out.</i>

20:24.192 --> 20:26.627
Do you think
Eric kills people with his gun?

20:29.931 --> 20:30.998
Probably.

20:32.667 --> 20:34.702
How many?

20:34.836 --> 20:36.771
Ten.

20:36.904 --> 20:38.005
Really?

20:39.674 --> 20:41.109
Yeah.

20:41.241 --> 20:43.010
Shot them right in the head.

20:43.144 --> 20:45.345
I mean, their brains explode
like spaghetti.

20:47.380 --> 20:48.883
I don't think he kills anyone.

21:12.740 --> 21:14.341
You can fix it, right?

21:15.243 --> 21:17.277
Yeah.

21:24.118 --> 21:25.753
Motherfucker!

21:31.491 --> 21:33.326
Fucking winch!

21:33.460 --> 21:34.996
Where am I going
to find a fucking winch?

21:45.472 --> 21:46.808
Remember
what we talked about.

21:48.976 --> 21:49.944
You take a breath.

21:51.411 --> 21:55.016
Exhale slowly.

21:58.085 --> 21:59.887
And whenever you're ready.

22:05.993 --> 22:07.061
Ha-ha! Nice shot.

22:09.530 --> 22:10.832
You're a natural.

22:23.343 --> 22:24.979
Look, uh,
it's none of my business,

22:25.112 --> 22:27.582
so you just tell me
to fuck right off

22:27.715 --> 22:28.916
if I'm overstepping.

22:30.518 --> 22:32.086
Is Alice okay with her
being out here?

22:34.021 --> 22:37.390
Yeah. Yeah, she's okay.
She's... she's fine.

22:44.065 --> 22:45.432
Alice is bipolar.

22:48.703 --> 22:50.638
A year ago, she was teaching
elementary school and...

22:51.772 --> 22:53.174
she had an episode

22:53.307 --> 22:55.643
and she thought a student
was somebody they weren't.

22:56.777 --> 22:58.112
And it was pretty bad.

22:59.180 --> 23:00.447
She...

23:00.581 --> 23:01.782
She just needs some time off.

23:01.916 --> 23:03.985
Get some rest.
Get her mind right.

23:04.118 --> 23:05.620
I mean, they put her
on this medication

23:05.753 --> 23:07.420
and it helps for a while,

23:07.555 --> 23:08.789
but she always gets worse.

23:11.525 --> 23:13.928
But up here, she seems good.

23:14.061 --> 23:15.129
You know?

23:15.263 --> 23:17.632
I think this is a really
good place for her.

23:17.765 --> 23:19.399
She's happy. We're happy.

23:47.228 --> 23:48.596
Chin up.

23:48.729 --> 23:50.631
You'll be a family
of mountain men in no time.

23:52.099 --> 23:53.634
Pioneers.

23:53.768 --> 23:55.970
Yeah.
We have all the help we can get.

24:06.213 --> 24:07.515
Do you have a winch?

24:09.917 --> 24:12.320
-Sweetheart, don't bother-
-I don't.

24:12.452 --> 24:14.454
But I might know
someone who does.

24:19.560 --> 24:20.795
I... I may need a favor.

24:33.774 --> 24:35.076
All right. How does it look?

24:35.209 --> 24:36.177
Is it tight?

24:36.310 --> 24:37.578
- Yep.
- Okay.

24:39.246 --> 24:41.148
I figure you can plug
that leak with a can of sealer

24:41.282 --> 24:42.683
and drop it
in the ground up there.

